{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Group"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"layoutPriority"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"value"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"parameters":[{"name":"value","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The priority by which a parent layout apportions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space to the child."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Views typically have a default priority of ","type":"text"},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which causes space to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"apportioned evenly to all sibling views. Raising a view’s layout","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"priority encourages the higher priority view to shrink later when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group is shrunk and stretch sooner when the group is stretched.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["HStack {","    Text(\"This is a moderately long string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .border(Color.gray)","","    Spacer()","","    Text(\"This is a higher priority string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .layoutPriority(1)","        .border(Color.gray)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the example above, the first ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"text":" element has the default","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"priority ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":" which causes its view to shrink dramatically due to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"higher priority of the second ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"text":" element, even though all of their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"other attributes (font, font size and character count) are the same.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A parent layout offers the child views with the highest layout priority","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all the space offered to the parent minus the minimum space required for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all its lower-priority children.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Sets the priority by which a parent layout should apportion space to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this child.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Group\/layoutPriority(_:)"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/group\/layoutpriority(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"name":"iOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"name":"macOS","beta":false,"depr